        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 3:57PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 356 PM CDT, Doppler radar wast tracking several gusty
thunderstorms across northeastern Illinois, moving northeastward
into northwestern Indiana at around 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and localed tree damage.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lake Station, St. Anne, Cedar Lake, Chesterton, Kankakee, Winfield,
Irwin, Valparaiso, Town of Pines, Lake Dalecarlia, Beverly Shores,
Merrillville, Hobart, Hopkins Park, Dunns Bridge, Hebron, Porter,
Dune Acres, Sun River Terrace, Grant Park, Wheeler, Lakes of the Four
Seasons, Gary, Kouts, and New Chicago.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
